<h1>@HI{{you ni suru}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vru{{}} @EM{{@HI{{you ni suru}}}}
<li> @Vnai{{}} @EM{{@HI{{you ni suru}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
These sentence patterns indicate that someone habitually or continuously makes efforts to do or not do something.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{tooth}}ni @KJ{{bad}}idesukara, @KJ{{sweet}}i@KJ{{thing}}wo @KJ{{eat}}benai
      @EM{{you ni shite imasu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I try not to eat sweets because they are bad for my teeth.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ashitaha @KJ{{discontinue^vis-a-vis}}ni @KJ{{time^interval}}ni @KJ{{slow}}renai
      @EM{{you ni shite}}kudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please be sure not to be late tomorrow.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@HI{{you ni shite imasu}} expresses a continuous or habitual effort to do something.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{you ni shite kudasai}} and @HI{{you ni shinaide kudasai}} are less direct and therefore more polite
than @Vte{{}} @HI{{kudasai}} and @Vnai{{}}@HI{{de kudasai}}.
</p>

